deck: Squirrel Girl's mom
description:
Origin

Little is known about Maureen Green. At some point she married Dor Green and gave birth to their daughter, Doreen.

Creation

Maureen Green was created by Ryan North and Erica Henderson. She made her first appearance in The Unbeatable Squirrel Girl #1.

Major Story Arcs

Squirrel Girl

Maureen travels to New York to visit her daughter. While Doreen is changing out of her costume, Maureen meets Doreen's roommate Nancy, and the pair bond over embarrassing stories about Doreen's childhood. When Brain Drain appears she is briefly taken hostage by him, but after he is defeated Maureen is able to convince Doreen and Nancy that he is harmless. She masquerades as his mother to badger the administration of Empire State University into allowing him to audit courses.

Powers and Abilities

Maureen has no known superhuman powers or abilities. She is a pretty chill lady, and a cool mom.
name: Maureen Green

deck: Jefferson Jackson is a football player and friend to Ronnie Raymond, the original Firestorm
description:
Other Media

The Flash

Jefferson "Jax" Jackson is played by Franz Drameh. After Ronnie Raymond sacrifices his life to save Central City from a black hole in the finale of Season 1, Martin Stein starts to have health issues. Martin and Ronnie were affected by the Particle Accelerator explosion and could combine to become Firestorm. Without Ronnie to combine with on a frequent basis, he starts dying. Cisco Ramon and Caitlin Snow try to find people who were affected by the explosion and could be compatible with the Firestorm Matrix. Their only compatible options were Henry Hewitt and Jefferson Jackson. They asked both if they would be willing to join Professor Stein as Firestorm but Jax wasn't interested and Henry was excited about it. Martin and Henry attempted to combine but it didn't work. Instead, it gave Henry nuclear superpowers and he became the villain known as Tokamak. Jax changes his mind and joins Martin and they become the new Firestorm. They team up with the Flash to take down Tokamak.

Legends of Tomorrow

Franz Drameh reprises his role as Jefferson Jackson. He and Martin Stein are enlisted by Rip Hunter onto his team to stop Vandal Savage from rising to power and taking over the world in the year 2166. Other members on the team include Hawkman, Hawkgirl, the Atom, White Canary, Captain Cold, and Heat Wave.
